data.title: Famous People & Places
data.text:
Alexander Gardiner - uploaded on 8/13/2013 12:49 PM

Alexander S. Gardiner (1835 -1914) farmer, merchant, businessman. Pickle mogul of Greenlawn.

Antoine de Saint-Exupéry - uploaded on 11/3/2014 5:39 PM

Antoine de Saint-Exupéry (1900-1944) French author and American pilot who died in WWII.

Arthur Dove & Helen Torr - uploaded on 8/13/2013 12:52 PM

Arthur Dove (1880-1946) and Helen Torr (1886-1967). American Modernist Painters.

August Heckscher - uploaded on 8/13/2013 1:04 PM

August Heckscher (1848-1941) Industrialist, Real Estate Developer & Philanthropist.

Bethel A.M.E. Church - uploaded on 8/13/2013 1:05 PM

Bethel African Methodist Episcopal Church (founded 1843) Park Avenue, Huntington.

Booker T. Washington - uploaded on 8/13/2013 1:11 PM

Booker T. Washington (1856-1915) Educator, Leader, founder of Tuskegee Institute.

Cornelius H. Delamater - uploaded on 8/13/2013 1:20 PM

Cornelius H. Delamater (1821-1889) of Eaton’s Neck, Farmer & Industrialist.

David Conklin Farm House - uploaded on 8/13/2013 1:24 PM

David Conklin (1743 – 1786) Farmer & Revolutionary War Patriot.

Dr. D.W. Kissam House - uploaded on 8/13/2013 1:14 PM

Daniel Whitehead Kissam (1763 – 1839) Colonial Era Physician.

Edward Thompson - uploaded on 8/13/2013 2:39 PM

Edward Thompson (1845-1923) Northport Entrepreneur & Lawbook Publisher.

First Purchase (1653) land for Town of Huntington bought from the Matinecock Indians.

Huntington’s Liberty Flag was first flown over the Village Green on July 22, 1776.

George Washington Brush (1842-1927) Dentist, Physician, Congressional Medal of Honor winner.

Harry Chapin - uploaded on 8/13/2013 4:33 PM

Harry Chapin (1942-1981) Singer, Songwriter, Humanitarian.

Henry L. Stimson - uploaded on 8/13/2013 4:38 PM

Henry L. Stimson (1867-1950) Lawyer, Diplomat, U. S. Secretary of War during WWII.

Henry Scudder - uploaded on 11/3/2014 5:28 PM

Henry Scudder (1743-1822) patriot of the American Revolution and NY State legislator.

Huntington Rural Cemetery - uploaded on 11/3/2014 5:31 PM

The Cemetery, located between NY Avenue & Oakwood Road, is incorporated March 1851.
